      "type": "vulnerability",
      "id": "vulnerability--bba2b547-7b59-4079-b7d3-92f57f294fdc",
      "name": "Triofox Unauthenticated Access Control Vulnerability",
      "description": "An unauthenticated access vulnerability in Gladinet\u2019s Triofox file-sharing and remote access platform (CVE-2025-12480) allowed attackers to bypass authentication and access configuration pages, enabling the upload and execution of arbitrary payloads. The vulnerability was exploited by manipulating the HTTP Host header to 'localhost', granting access to privileged setup pages.",
      "created": "2025-11-10T00:00:00Z",
      "modified": "2025-11-10T00:00:00Z",
      "external_references": [
        {
          "source_name": "CVE",
